FT  10 JAN 92 / World News in Brief: Hospital outbreak kills 5
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Five elderly patients died after an outbreak of a bowel infection at North
Manchester General Hospital. Two wards have been closed. During the outbreak
15 people died, but only five of the deaths were directly related to the
infection.
